== 用途 ==
The [[稳定同位素|稳定同位素]] composition of a belemnoid rostrum from the [[Peedee_Formation|Peedee Formation]] ([[Cretaceous|Cretaceous]], southeast USA) has long been used as a global standard (Peedee Belemnite, "PDB") against which other [[isotope_geochemistry|isotope geochemistry]] samples are measured, for both [[碳同位素|碳同位素]] and [[氧同位素|氧同位素]].

Some belemnoids (such as ''Belemnites'' of [[Belemnitida|Belemnitida]]) serve as [[index_fossil|index fossil]]s, particularly in the Cretaceous [[Chalk_Formation|Chalk Formation]] of Europe, enabling [[geologist|geologist]]s to date the age the [[rock_(geology)|rocks]] in which they are found.

